425 "§16-5-56
426 Any person individual or institution aggrieved by not
427 satisfied with the actions of the commission in its
428 administration of the program, by may submit a written
429 petition filed with to the commission within 30 days after
430 notice of the action complained of, may request a rehearing by
431 the commission. If not satisfied with the response of the
432 commission to the written petition, the individual or
433 institution may request a rehearing within 20 days after the
434 response of the commission is made. The commission shall
435 schedule the requested rehearing not less than 20, nor more
436 than 30, within 20 days after receipt of the petition
