438 institution may present written and oral evidence supporting
439 its the petition and may be represented by counsel. The
440 decision of the commission following the rehearing shall be is
441 final."
442 Section 2. Sections 16-5-53.1 and16-5-53.2 are added to
443 the Code of Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
444 §16-5-53.1
445 (a) The commission shall develop an accountability and
446 evaluation plan for the program that does all of the
447 following:
448 (1) Identifies the goals, objectives, and expected
Page 16

(1) Identifies the goals, objectives, and expected
SB74 INTRODUCED
449 outputs and outcomes of the program.
450 (2) Describes the specific activities of the program
451 and how those activities will achieve expected outcomes.
452 (3) Defines what the expected metrics of success shall
453 be and provides a monitoring plan to regularly assess
454 performance.
455 (4) Provides an evaluation plan to assess the impact of
456 expected outcomes.
457 (b) The commission shall consult with the Alabama
458 Commission on the Evaluation of Services on the development of
459 the accountability and evaluation plan.
460 §16-5-53.2
461 Any eligible applicant who met the requirements of the
462 program and received a loan repayment prior to August 1, 2026,
463 shall remain eligible for loan repayments pursuant to the
464 requirements of the program as long as they remain
465 continuously employed with a qualifying school.
466 Section 3. Section 16-5-54.2, Code of Alabama 1975,
467 relating to documentation required from educators who received
468 their certifications pursuant to an alternative certification
469 program to receive loan repayments under AMSTEP, is repealed.
470 Section 4. This act shall become effective on August 1,
471 2026.
